cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
title: "Chinese Classical Bench"
abstract: >-
  A benchmark for Classical Chinese language understanding in LLMs:
  6 tasks (translation, punctuation restoration, character glossing,
  allusion sourcing, single-character cloze, modern-to-classical compression)
  x 100 questions = 600, sampled from a CC0 corpus of the Thirteen Classics,
  Shuowen Jiezi, Zizhi Tongjian, and the first 15 of the Twenty-Four Histories.
authors:
  - name: "gujilab"
repository-code: "https://github.com/gujilab/chinese-classical-bench"
url: "https://huggingface.co/datasets/gujilab/chinese-classical-bench"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - classical-chinese
  - 文言文
  - benchmark
  - evaluation
  - large-language-models
version: "1.1"
date-released: "2026-05-14"
